--- Notes ---
1. Step 10 loss (3.08) is high because the warmup has just completed
   and the model has not yet encountered the domain vocabulary.
2. Rapid drop to 1.52 by step 30 corresponds to the adapter learning
   the basic chat-template structure and closing greeting format.
3. Plateau from step 60 onward (0.68 → 0.42 over 20 steps) is the
   adapter fine-tuning tone register — the slower learning here is
   expected for style rather than structural features.
4. Effective batch size of 8 was the T4 maximum without OOM; larger
   batches produced CUDA out-of-memory at batch_size=4 (effective 16).
